data.enText: including all the things or people that are involved in a particular situation; general
the person with overall responsibility for the project

data.chText: 三个年龄组将各产生一位优胜者，另有一位总优胜者。
data.enText: There will be winners in each of three age groups, and one overall winner .
an overall improvement in standards of living (= affecting everyone)

data.chText: 画完以后，她退后一步，以审视总体效果。
data.enText: When she finished painting, she stepped back to admire the overall effect .
including everything or everyone; in total

data.chText: 这个公司将总计投资160万元购置新设备。
data.enText: The company will invest $1.6m overall in new equipment.

data.chText: 一般来说；大致上；总体上
总的来说，这是一本很有用的书。
data.enText: Overall, this is a very useful book.
a loose coat worn over other clothes to protect them from dirt, etc.

data.chText: 实验室助手穿着一件白罩衣。
data.enText: The lab assistant was wearing a white overall.
a loose piece of clothing like a shirt and trousers/pants in one piece, made of heavy cloth and usually worn over other clothing by workers doing dirty work

data.chText: 机修工穿着一件蓝色工装连衣裤。
data.enText: The mechanic was wearing a pair of blue overalls.

tr: (usually plural) work clothing consisting of denim trousers (usually with a bib and shoulder straps)
a loose protective coverall or smock worn over ordinary clothing for dirty work

example: the overall pattern of his life

value.boxr_value: The adjective and adverb are pronounced  /ˌəʊvər'ɔːl/. The noun is pronounced /'əʊvərɔːl/. 形容词和副词读作 /ˌəʊvər'ɔːl/。名词读作 /'əʊvərɔːl/。

value.def: You use overall to indicate that you are talking about a situation in general or about the whole of something.

example.ex: Cut down your overall amount of physical activity...
It is usually the woman who assumes overall care of the baby.
example.tran: 通常由女性负责照顾孩子的方方面面。

example.ex: Overall, I like Connie. I think she's great...
example.tran: 总的说来，我喜欢康妮，我认为她人挺不错。

example.ex: The college has few ways to assess the quality of education overall.
example.tran: 总体看来，这所大学评估教育质量的方法寥寥无几。

value.def: Overalls consist of a single piece of clothing that combines trousers and a jacket. You wear overalls over your clothes in order to protect them while you are working.

example.tran: 穿着蓝色连身工作服的工人

value.def: Overalls are trousers that are attached to a piece of cloth which covers your chest and which has straps going over your shoulders.

example.ex: An elderly man dressed in faded overalls took the witness stand.
example.tran: 一位穿着褪色吊带工装裤的老人上了证人席。

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, use 英国英语用 dungarees

value.def: An overall is a piece of clothing shaped like a coat that you wear over your clothes in order to protect them while you are working.
